	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64607155">For most of us, I expect, it was the increasingly crushing workload of maintaining legacy code bases...
In several places <p>
I have worked, starting from PDP11s, New code was put in the public domain to avoid the need to maintain it. (Google: DECUS).</p><p>

It was useful code, and others would not just maintain it but grow the functionality, once it was able to run wild and free. </p><p>Trivial utilities grew to be great wild beasts.</p><p>
The secret of success was to keep the PHBs in the dark.</p></div>
	</div>

